<div class="body-background">

<div class="results-title">
OK <%= @home.name %>, here are your numbers!<br>
</div>

<% loan = (@home.asking_price.to_i + @home.asking_price.to_i * @home.seller_con.to_i/100) * 0.965 %>
<% i = (1 + @home.rate.to_f/100/12)**(12/12)-1 %>
<% annuity = (1-(1/(1+i))**360)/i %>

<div class="results-p1">
You told me the asking price is <%= number_to_currency(@home.asking_price) %>
and the seller's concession is <%= @home.seller_con %> which equates to <%= number_to_currency(@home.asking_price.to_i * @home.seller_con.to_f/100) %><br>
Therefore, your purchase contract will be for <%= number_to_currency(@home.asking_price.to_i + @home.asking_price.to_i * @home.seller_con.to_i/100) %>
</div>

<div class="results-p2">
Assuming you are applying for an FHA loan, the maximum you can borrow is 96.50% of the value. This is also known as the loan to value ratio. <br>
So, if your purchase contract is <%= number_to_currency(@home.asking_price.to_i + @home.asking_price.to_i * @home.seller_con.to_i/100) %>, and you can borrow 96.50% of that, you can mortgage up to <%= number_to_currency((@home.asking_price.to_i + @home.asking_price.to_i * @home.seller_con.to_i/100) * 0.965) %>.<br><br>

Your minimum downpayment is <%= number_to_currency((@home.asking_price.to_i + @home.asking_price.to_i * @home.seller_con.to_i/100) - ((@home.asking_price.to_i + @home.asking_price.to_i * @home.seller_con.to_i/100) * 0.965)) %>
</div>


<div class="results-p3">
Based off of the interest rate of <%= @home.rate %> and a 30 year loan, your monthly mortgage payment will be

<%= payment = number_to_currency(loan/annuity) %> <br><br>

Other Expenses:<br>
You told me the Real Estate taxes are: <%= number_to_currency(@home.re_taxes) %> per year<br>
Based on US national average data, I have estimated your Homeowner's Insurance to be <%= hinsurance = number_to_currency(0.0035*loan) %> per year<br><br>

Total:<br>
Your total Mortgage Payment including Principle, Interest, Taxes and Insurance will be <%= number_to_currency((@home.re_taxes.to_i/12) + (0.0035*loan/12) + (loan/annuity)) %> per month<br><br>
</div>

<div class="results-p4">
Can you Qualify?<br>
In order to purchase this home, you will need to show income of <%= number_to_currency(((@home.re_taxes.to_i/12) + (0.0035*loan/12) + (loan/annuity)) / ( 0.43)) %> a month
</div>

<br><br>

<%= link_to 'Edit', edit_home_path(@home) %> |
<%= link_to 'Back', homes_path %>

</div>
